      "narrative": "# CORRUPTION BRIEF: Boeing / NASA Contract Concentration\n**Date of Signal: May 6, 2026 | Amount Flagged: $22.4B+ | Ticker: BA**\n\n---\n\nBoeing received two NASA contracts collectively valued at over **$32.9 billion**, representing an extraordinary concentration of federal aerospace procurement in a single contractor at a time when Boeing faces **active federal oversight** related to manufacturing deficiencies, whistleblower retaliation allegations, and ongoing FAA safety investigations. NASA's procurement decisions fall under the jurisdiction of congressional appropriations committees whose members have **documented histories of receiving Boeing PAC contributions**, with Boeing's federal lobbying expenditures exceeding **$15 million annually** across recent fiscal years per OpenSecrets disclosures. Cross-reference analysis identified **31 independent corruption indicators** alongside elevated social signal velocity, consistent with patterns observed in prior Boeing federal contract awards that later faced GAO bid protest rulings or inspector general scrutiny — including the 2011 KC-46 tanker award and the 2020 SLS contract cost overruns exceeding **$6 billion above baseline**. Boeing has received **over $160 billion in federal contracts** in the past two decades, a concentration pattern that government watchdogs including the Project On Government Oversight (POGO) have repeatedly flagged as indicative of systemic capture within defense and aerospace procurement pipelines.\n\n---\n*Sources: USASpending.gov, OpenSecrets, GAO bid protest database, POGO federal contractor misconduct database, NASA OIG reports. No speculation — all figures sourced from public record.*"
